         <div type="translation" resp="#cmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p>For emperor Caesar Lucius Septimius Severus Pius Pertinax Augustus,  holding tribunician power for the ninth time, acclaimed victor?  times, consul twice, 
               father of the country, and emperor Caesar Marcus Aurelius Antoninus Augustus, holding tribunician power for the fourth time, consul, and Lucius <note>erased</note> 
               Septimius Geta <note>erased</note> Caesar Augustus set up under Quintus Anicius Faustus, legate of the Augusti, consular commander  of legion III Augusta, Pia, Vindex <note>erased from legion</note>.</p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <!-- <p>Line 2:  tribunician power for the ninth time: 10 Dec. 200 - 9 Dec. 201.</p>
            <p>Geta Augustus: see on <ref type="inscription" n="IRT0913">913</ref>.</p> -->
            <p>Quintus Anicius Faustus: <title>PIR</title> A 0595, <ref target="https://pir.bbaw.de/id/1300">https://pir.bbaw.de/id/1300</ref></p>
            <p>One of the four inscriptions over the gates of the camp: <ref type="inscription" n="IRT0914">914</ref>, <ref type="inscription" n="IRT0915">915</ref>, <ref type="inscription" n="IRT0916">916</ref>, 
               <ref type="inscription" n="IRT1030">1030</ref></p>
